text=(:title Experience:)%0ahttp://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/images/city_savannah.png%0a!Experience (XP)%0aThis guide will walk you through the basics of earning and spending experience to build your characters. Some venues may have specific guidelines that enhance the following information, so be sure to check your venue's Player Guide.%0a%0a!!Earning Experience:%0a%0a3 XP is awarded weekly to sanctioned characters. This experience is awarded on Fridays.%0a%0a!!!Bonus Experience:%0a%0aSanctioned characters may earn up to a maximum of 5 bonus XP per month. %0a%0aBonus XP may be earned primarily through activity, such as exceptional role play in Storyteller lead scenes, exceptional blue-booking (attached to requests), or helping the setting or venue to flourish through creative contributions. Bonus XP is awarded at ST discretion.%0a%0aPlayers may also choose to donate money to the site. A donation of $5 per month (per character) will be converted to 5 bonus experience at the rate of $1 for 1 XP. See [[$5 for 5 Offer]] for more details.%0a%0aBonus XP earned through activity or donation cannot be stacked to receive more than 5 Bonus XP per month.%0a%0a!!Spending Experience%0a%0aTo spend your XP, you need to submit a request to your Storyteller(s) through the Request System. The Request System is designed to faciliate communication between you and your Storyteller(s). (For those who are familiar with "Character Threads," this is the newer, shinier version!) Only your venue Storyteller(s) can modify your sheet, so please don't ask anyone else to do it.%0a%0aThe same statistic cannot be raised two months in a row. %0a%0aA request requires a number of justifications equal to it's dot rating halved, round up. (1,1,2,2,3).%0a%0aA justification is a significant piece of your characters story that displays work towards, use of, or improvement of the item requested. Examples include: Scenes with storytellers, Logs of scenes with players, Bluebooking, teaching from an appropriate mentor and potentially other unthought-of methods created by players and approved by storytellers.%0a%0aSTs will sometimes waive some or all of the justification requirements. This usually involves some kind of supernatural intervention (like goblin markets), material acquisitions (in the case of items/havens/retainers etc), or extraordinary circumstances.%0a%0aVenue specific items (supernatural powers/abilities, merits, power stats etc) may require different criteria to the above guide. These criteria are defined by the storytellers of the venue.
