n your last XP Spending request, you cannot raise it in your next request.%0a> * 1 dot: You can earn new skills at 1 dot weekly.%0a> * 2 dot: To raise a skill from 1 to 2 requires 1 month of training time. You can work on multiple 2-dot skills at once.%0a> * 3 dot: To raise a skill from 2 to 3 requires 2 months of training time.%0a> * 4 dot: To raise a skill from 3 to 4 requires 4 months of training time.%0a> * 5 dot: To raise a skill from 4 to 5 requires 8 months of training time.%0a> %0a> !!!Merits and Flaws%0a> * Gaining a merit or losing a flaw requires justification.%0a> * Some merits, such as Status, may have specific requirements. See your Storyteller(s).%0a> %0a> !!!Morality (etc.) and Willpower%0a> * In addition to XP cost, raising these traits requires exceptional and consistant role play.%0a> * These can also be decreased through role play.%0a> %0a> !!!Supernatural Traits%0a> * This includes: Blood Potency, Gnosis, Primal Urge, Wyrd, as well as Arcana, Contracts, Disciplines, Gifts, Forbidden Lore, etc.%0a> *Only one Supernatural trait can be raised at a time, and it cannot be raised consecutively.%0a> %0a> !!!Mentors and Other Tricks of the Trade%0a> IC Mentors (NPC or PC) can reduce training time in half for skills, and are excellent means of justification for most experience spends.%0a> %0a> There may be other (sometimes mystical) means of improving your character, and you're encouraged to explore this opportunity In Character if you're willing to pay the price in addition to XP.%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
