diff:1372686562:1372686562:=1,56d0%0a%3c !!Earning Experience %0a%3c Experience is awarded weekly at a time to be determined. %0a%3c %0a%3c Characters can recieve up to 0 xp per week until determined. %0a%3c %0a%3c Characters can also earn bonus XP in scenes, at ST discretion. This will normally be 1 Experience Point. The general criteria is that you have to blow the ST's socks off. Visit [[Character Update Threads]] to view details about how your character requests/updates should be formatted. %0a%3c %0a%3c A character may earn up to 5 bonus XP in a month (this doesn't count Arcane Experience for Mages). %0a%3c %0a%3c !!Spending Experience %0a%3c When your character is sanctioned, you will be directed to make a thread for your character in one of the Character Update forums (they are grouped by gameline). This thread will be private, and only you and STs can read it. %0a%3c %0a%3c Post your experience expenditures to your update thread in a single post between the 1st and the 7th of every month. You can only spend XP once a month and your Storyteller will grant or reject your request by the 15th of the month. It is very helpful for players to make their Experience requests stand out in some way, either by having them be in bold or italics lettering or by marking them as a different color than the rest of their posts to the update thread. %0a%3c %0a%3c Every experience expenditure should be justified, either through IC actions or in-character posts to your update thread where you may detail what your character does during the game’s “downtime.” Your justifications need not be verbose or extremely detailed, they should, however, make sense and be true to the story. %0a%3c %0a%3c Only your Storyteller can modify your sheet, so please don't ask anyone else to do it. %0a%3c %0a%3c !!Character Advancement %0a%3c Please keep the following in mind when making your Experience requests: %0a%3c %0a%3c '''Attributes:''' You cannot consecutively increase any Trait in the Attribute category. For example: If Troy increases Stamina, he cannot request to increase Stamina or any other Attribute (Presence, Intelligence, Dexterity, etc) in his next Experience expenditure. %0a%3c %0a%3c '''Skills:''' You cannot consecutively increase the same Skill. This includes learning a Skill Specialty. For example: If Troy learns the “Daggers” Specialty for Weaponry, he cannot request an increase in Weaponry or another Specialty in Weaponry on his next Experience expenditure. %0a%3c %0a%3c '''Merits:''' Tiered Merits cannot be increased consecutively, just like Attributes and Skills. Tiered Merits are those which have varying values in which each dot conveys a new degree of power or influence (Fighting Styles, Allies & Contacts, etc.). Also remember that a Merit’s cost is cumulative, for example the 4-dot Quick Healer Merit costs 20 XP (1x2 + 2x2 + 3x2 + 4x2 = 20 XP). This creates a balance so that all Merits of the same level will (eventually) cost the same amount of XP. (see World of Darkness, p 108) %0a%3c %0a%3c '''Morality & Willpower:''' These are special advantages that can decrease and increase during the course of the story. In addition to the Experience cost, exceptional and consistent roleplay should be used to justify an increase in these Traits. %0a%3c %0a%3c '''Supernatural Traits:''' These are defined as powers or Traits derived from donning one of the supernatural templates that includes changelings, mages, vampires and werewolves. Supernatural Traits are defined as: Blood Potency, Gnosis, Primal Urge and Wyrd; additionally, all Arcana, Contracts, Disciplines and Gifts. %0a%3c %0a%3c Only one Supernatural Trait can be increased at a time. This represents the focus and dedication required to study or experience the mystic aspects of a character’s own abilities. %0a%3c %0a%3c The same Supernatural Trait cannot be learned consecutively. For example: Troy gains Blood Potency 4, he cannot request Blood Potency 5 in his next Experience expenditure. Likewise, should he gain Protean 2 in his following request, the next request could be for any other Discipline or even Blood Potency 5, but he will not be granted the next level of Protean. %0a%3c %0a%3c '''Special Considerations: '''%0a%3c %0a%3c *'''Blood Sorceries:''' The sanguinary magics of the kindred, such as Cruac or Theban Sorcery, can only be learned when the character has the appropriate influence within her Covenant. This means that a character must have at least one dot in the relevant Covenant status in order to learn the relevant blood sorcery. Furthermore, once play begins you must have an appropriate Mentor to purchase rituals or dots of the discipline.  If you do not have a Mentor, you can still purchase dots of the sorcery, but must also pay experience for the usual "free" ritual.  For instance, if Lestat can't get a mentor but wishes to purchase Theban Sorcery 1 with Blood Scourge as his first ritual, he must spend 9 XP instead of the usual 7 XP.  You cannot learn additional rituals without a mentor, but you can invent or discover them on your own (see below).  Also, you may need to purchase Status.  For more information, see [[VampireHouseRules|Vampire House Rules]].%0a%3c %0a%3c **Furthermore, a Kindred can only learn a number of rituals equal to the lower of her Intelligence or Resolve at one time. This represents the character’s focus and commitment to being able to retain and understand these esoteric secrets.%0a%3c %0a%3c **To invent or discover their own rituals, a character must have a Discipline rating of one higher than the ritual she wishes to create.  For instance, to create a level 2 Cruac ritual, Aaliyah has to have Cruac 3.  Submit the ritual to us via your thread and we will work with you to get it into play.%0a%3c  %0a%3c *'''Devotions:''' Devotions must be learned from a teacher. This means a character needs at least one dot in the Mentor Merit to learn vampiric devotions. Keep in mind that a Mentor’s rating not only accounts for that Mentor’s influence in your character’s life but their ability and willingness to teach ever-more useful things to your character. Characters (and their players) can still develop their own unique Devotions, though it is a difficult process. %0a%3c %0a%3c *'''Rituals & Renown:''' Once play begins, Uratha can only learn rites from a teacher. This means a character needs at least one dot in the Mentor Merit after Character Creation.%0a%3c  %0a%3c **''Earning Renown in game:'' Renown is recognition not only by one's peers, but by the spirits that serve Mother Moon herself. And, it takes work and dedication to achieve. Players will be required to maintain their character threads and note when their character has performed deeds worthy of Renown (see Werewolf: The Forsaken, p 194-197). Once they have the XP for a Renown increase, they will make their case to the ST who can judge the uratha's worthiness compared to their past deeds. The ST will inform the player that a new dot of the appropriate Renown can be purchased with XP, providing they can find someone to perform the required rite. %0a%3c %0a%3c **As deeds worthy of renown become more difficult to achieve the more known and experienced your werewolf becomes, it will be important for the player to keep a very close eye on their character's noteworthy achievements and, most importantly, record them in the Character Update Thread. %0a%3c %0a%3c *'''Rotes & Arcana:''' Mages must have access to teachers and/or grimoires to learn additional rotes once play begins. A character must have at least one dot in the Mentor Merit and/or one dot of Status in her Order (should she belong to one). A Mentor or Order's willingness to teach rotes is based upon the relationship with the student. Students or members with better standing (ie, higher ratings in the aforementioned Merits) are privy to greater secrets (higher level rotes). This rule does not apply to player characters learning from other player characters, but the social ramifications of teaching rotes outside of one’s own Order should always be at the forefront of every magi’s mind. %0a%3c %0a%3c **Free Council characters are an exception to this rule. The Free Council will teach any member of their Order rotes of any level, regardless of their Status. It's rumored that the Free Council will even share knowledge with their allies.%0a%3c %0a%3c **Furthermore, a mage can only learn a number of rotes equal to the lower of her Intelligence or Resolve at one time. This represents the character’s focus and commitment to being able to retain and understand these esoteric secrets.%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
